dvanced supplementation
As part of your Age Management Program we analyse key nutrients in your body. Your nutritional
assessment provides evidence which helps us tailor Advanced Supplements to meet your individual needs.
Note: Vitamin, Mineral, Amino Acids, Antioxidants, Minerals, Fatty Acids and Digestive Enzymes can be measured with our
Complete Nutritional Analysis.
Total protein
contains a variety of proteins that perform important metabolic
functions. Blood proteins transport molecules, promote blood clotting and help your
immune system. (Having a high protein count could be the sign of a serious disease).
Albumen
is tested to check how well the liver and kidneys are working, and to
fnd out if your diet contains enough protein( Microalbuminuria is useful to assess
kidney damage in Cardiometabolic disease).
Globulin
is tested to determine the health of your immune system and your
chances of developing an infection.
Magnesium
Often lacking. Key role in heart rhythm, nervous system, relaxation,
muscles and bone health and sugar control.
Calcium
blood calcium helps screen for a range of conditions relating to bones,
heart, nerves, kidneys, and teeth. (Also important for acid/alkali balance and
coagulation of blood.)
Uric Acid
Practical way to determine how sensitive you are to fructose consumption.
Targeted Nutraceuticals will lower your blood sugar.
Vitamin B12
is essential for the prevention of certain forms of anemia and
neurological disturbances. It is also involved in fat and carbohydrate metabolism
and is essential for optimal hormonal balance and growth.
Ferritin
is a protein that stores iron in your bodys tissues. It is an indicator of
your bodys iron stores. Very high or low levels produce fatigue and other illness.
